extends layout

block content
  style.
    .support-container {
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 800px;
      padding: 40px 20px;
      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
      font-size: 15px;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #222;
    }
    .support-container h1 {
      font-size: 28px;
      margin-bottom: 4px;
    }
    .support-container .subtitle {
      color: #666;
      font-size: 15px;
      margin-bottom: 40px;
    }
    .support-container h2 {
      font-size: 20px;
      margin-top: 40px;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
      padding-bottom: 6px;
    }
    .support-container p {
      font-size: 15px;
      margin: 12px 0;
      color: #444;
    }
    .faq-card {
      background: #f5f5f7;
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 20px;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
    .faq-card h3 {
      font-size: 16px;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: #1c1c1e;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }
    .faq-card p {
      margin: 6px 0;
    }
    .faq-card code {
      background: #e5e5ea;
      border-radius: 4px;
      padding: 1px 5px;
      font-size: 13px;
    }
    .contact-block {
      background: #f5f5f7;
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 20px;
      margin-top: 16px;
    }
    .contact-block p {
      margin: 4px 0;
    }

  .support-container
    h1 Fit With Friends Support
    p.subtitle Get help with competitions, activity data, and more.

    h2 Competitions

    .faq-card
      h3 How do I create a competition?
      p
        | Go to the home screen and tap
        strong  Create new competition.
        |  Give it a name and set the duration (1–30 days). Once created, tap the
        strong  &hellip;
        |  button on the competition and select
        strong  Share
        |  to generate an invite link you can send to friends.

    .faq-card
      h3 How do I join a competition?
      p Ask the competition admin to share the invite link with you. Tapping the link will open Fit with Friends and show a confirmation screen. Confirm to join and you'll appear on the leaderboard immediately.

    .faq-card
      h3 How does scoring work?
      p
        | You earn one point for each percent of each activity ring you close. For example: 50% Move + 125% Exercise + 75% Stand = 250 points for that day. The maximum is
        strong  600 points per day
        |  (100% on all three rings counts as 300; going beyond 100% on any ring earns bonus points up to the cap).
      p Since points are based on your personal ring goals set in Apple Health, make sure your goals are set to a realistic level so competitions stay fair.

    .faq-card
      h3 How many competitions can I be in at once?
      p
        | Free accounts can be in up to
        strong  1 active private competition
        |  at a time. Upgrading to
        strong  Fit with Friends Pro
        |  raises this limit to 10, and also unlocks access to public community competitions.

    h2 Activity Data Troubleshooting

    .faq-card
      h3 My activity data isn't being counted
      p First, check that Fit with Friends has permission to read all required Apple Health categories:
      p
        code Settings &rsaquo; Privacy &amp; Security &rsaquo; Health &rsaquo; Fit with Friends
      p Make sure all categories are enabled. Then close and re-launch the app.

    .faq-card
      h3 Data updates while the app is open but not in the background
      p Enable Background App Refresh for the app:
      p
        code Settings &rsaquo; Fit with Friends &rsaquo; Background App Refresh
      p With this enabled, your rings will sync automatically throughout the day without needing to open the app.

    h2 Contact

    p
      | Can't find what you're looking for? Send us an email and we'll get back to you.

    .contact-block
      p Fit With Friends
      p
        a(href='mailto:fitwithfriendsapp@gmail.com') fitwithfriendsapp@gmail.com
